    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "8577b1be_41cfcd88",
        "filename": "util/stream/base94_output_stream.cc",
        "patchSetId": 3
      },
      "lineNbr": 167,
      "author": {
        "id": 1133706
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-10-23T10:16:32Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Although this produces the right output, I think is not really the most clear way to write it.\n\nBefore this point, bit_count_ is definitely \u003c 8, and we must have one symbol to decode that fills the remaining buffer up to 8 bits (it can\u0027t be more than that because each symbol can only provide 6.6 bits). Adding 8 to bit_count_ doesn\u0027t give a correct value; it just makes the loop execute once.\n\nI\u0027d advise removing the loop, and references to bit_count_ and leaving just:\n\n  buffer_.push_back(bit_buf_ \u0026 0xff);\n  bit_buf_ \u003e\u003e\u003d 8;\n  DCHECK(!bit_buf_)",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 167,
        "startChar": 2,
        "endLine": 167,
        "endChar": 18
      },
      "revId": "d0ab843d8e3f415726574424a658de29f4b80b05",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
